  "text": "## Fetch API WebIDL to C++ Binding Mapping\n\nThe following mappings show the WebIDL interface definitions and their corresponding C++ binding implementations for the Fetch API in Firefox:\n\n### 1. Request Interface\n- **WebIDL**: `dom/webidl/Request.webidl` - Defines the Request interface per the Fetch specification (https://fetch.spec.whatwg.org/#request-class)\n- **C++ Header**: `dom/fetch/Request.h` - Contains the Request class declaration that extends FetchBody<Request> and implements the WebIDL interface\n- **C++ Implementation**: `dom/fetch/Request.cpp` - Contains the implementation of the Request class and all WebIDL-exposed methods\n\n### 2. Response Interface\n- **WebIDL**: `dom/webidl/Response.webidl` - Defines the Response interface per the Fetch specification (https://fetch.spec.whatwg.org/#response-class)\n- **C++ Header**: `dom/fetch/Response.h` - Contains the Response class declaration that extends FetchBody<Response> and implements the WebIDL interface\n- **C++ Implementation**: `dom/fetch/Response.cpp` - Contains the implementation of the Response class and all WebIDL-exposed methods\n\n### 3. Headers Interface\n- **WebIDL**: `dom/webidl/Headers.webidl` - Defines the Headers interface for HTTP header manipulation (http://fetch.spec.whatwg.org/#headers-class)\n- **C++ Header**: `dom/fetch/Headers.h` - Contains the Headers class declaration that wraps InternalHeaders and implements the WebIDL interface\n- **C++ Implementation**: `dom/fetch/Headers.cpp` - Contains the implementation of the Headers class and all WebIDL-exposed methods\n\n### 4. FetchEvent Interface\n- **WebIDL**: `dom/webidl/FetchEvent.webidl` - Defines the FetchEvent interface for service worker fetch event handling (http://slightlyoff.github.io/ServiceWorker/spec/service_worker/index.html)\n- **C++ Header**: `dom/serviceworkers/ServiceWorkerEvents.h` - Contains the FetchEvent class declaration that extends ExtendableEvent (line 132-147)\n- **C++ Implementation**: `dom/serviceworkers/ServiceWorkerEvents.cpp` - Contains the implementation of the FetchEvent class and all WebIDL-exposed methods\n\nAll these interfaces are exported to both Window and Worker scopes (except FetchEvent which is exported only to ServiceWorker scope). The C++ implementations use Mozilla's WebIDL bindings framework to automatically generate JavaScript bindings that expose these interfaces to web content."
}

